</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="13" pageId="12" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="12.[685,1173,991,1729]" pageId="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,824,1682,1703]" pageId="12">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a Latin compound name that stems from 
<emphasis box="[1008,1064,1708,1729]" italics="true" pageId="12">flavus</emphasis>
(= yellow)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[173,659,194,242]" pageId="13">
and 
<emphasis box="[218,263,194,215]" italics="true" pageId="13">apex</emphasis>
(= tip) and refers to the yellow tip of the antenna.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
